_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]) to cover. In addition to the grid itse=
lf, each individual home, factory, and office had to be wired to receive an=
d utilize the electrons that the grid delivers. That takes investment, buy-=
in, and time. Lots of time.
The project continues, and will continue. Infrastructure projects are endle=
ssly expansive.
But the current state of things is that when you move into a building =E2=
=80=93 a home, an office, a warehouse, a store, any building really =E2=80=
=93 it=E2=80=99s already wired up for electricity. The electricity comes wi=
th the building. You just move in, sign up, and turn on.
That is not how the internet works for companies, yet.
While each building has internet from one or more ISPs running into it, a w=
orking network doesn=E2=80=99t just come with the building.
The network is customized from scratch each time: new ISP contract, new net=
work design, new hardware, new security, new software. IT teams work with a=
