other designs the network, another sells the hardware (either directly or a=
s a value-added reseller), another installs, and yet another provides the s=
oftware to monitor, manage, and configure the network as a company=E2=80=99=
s needs inevitably change (managed service provider, or MSP).
And the system works well enough! You=E2=80=99re probably reading this from=
 office WiFi that=E2=80=99s working just fine.
There is some really good networking hardware out there. Cisco=E2=80=99s Me=
raki is the leader in the space. Meraki generates somewhere between $5-10 b=
illion, and is growing fast. Ruckus makes great access points. Palo Alto Ne=
tworks makes great security hardware and software; it=E2=80=99s worth $125 =
billion. Arista makes great switches; it=E2=80=99s worth $136 billion.
That hardware can be CapEx intensive, sure, but as an IT leader at Dollar G=
eneral told a Tegus interviewer [ https://substack.com/redirect/048f380c-ec=
a1-49c5-a46d-a50c8a639037?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepK=
bqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], retailers often prefer CapEx over OpEx because they ca=
n amortize the costs over time.
Managed Service Providers do a robust book of business, too. The global MSP=
 market for networking alone is something like $70-80 billion [ https://sub=
stack.com/redirect/205c252a-60c7-4e98-85d0-c9fd99feaa47?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3Q=
ifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] and expected to grow at a=
n 8% CAGR, much faster than the 3% growth CIOs expect [ https://substack.co=
m/redirect/792eefc8-e9ec-412b-97ca-718c171efc8c?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J=
5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] for internal IT teams. It=E2=80=
=99s more fragmented, but huge.
Certainly, setting up and managing a network can still be a pain for IT tea=
ms. It=E2=80=99s more expensive than it probably should be. A MSP can=E2=80=
=99t build the kind of software to manage networks that a company could if =
the company also built the hardware.
All of which is to say, the internet is not yet a utility, but it does work=
=2E
