on IP addresses.
The packet is born.
Like a neonatal nurse, the network interface driver takes the newly born pa=
cket and swaddles it in an Ethernet frame. Thus wrapped, the packet is sent=
 to the network interface card (NIC), which converts the digital frame into=
 analog signals =E2=80=93 for copper wires, electric signals; for fiber-opt=
ic cables, light pulses; for WiFi, radio waves =E2=80=93 and transmits them=
