At this point, our packet=E2=80=99s journey looks almost like the journey o=
f an electron from generation facility to service panel. In this analogy, t=
he backbone is like the transmission line =E2=80=93 it=E2=80=99s the big bu=
ndles of fiber-optic cables, buried underground or under the sea [ https://=
substack.com/redirect/7f0ce799-67dd-444e-b6bb-49d0a9365c7e?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAw=
Z3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], over which data trave=
ls very long distances. It reaches the ISP=E2=80=99s border router, and ent=
