The core network is a place where the internet truly becomes the "network o=
f networks." Here, routers belonging to Tier 1 ISPs=E2=80=94the largest int=
ernet providers in the world=E2=80=94exchange data using Border Gateway Pro=
tocol (BGP), the postal system of the internet that decides which paths dat=
a packets should take based on a combination of policy, economics, and effi=
ciency. The border router uses BGP to determine the packet=E2=80=99s next h=
