yle=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size:=
 16px;">Our intrepid packet, now a seasoned traveler at the ripe old age of=
 50 milliseconds, plunges into the depths of the ocean. It's carried along =
undersea fiber optic cables, a network of glass threads crisscrossing the o=
cean floor like the neural pathways of a global brain. These cables, each n=
o thicker than a garden hose, carry 97% of intercontinental data traffic. O=
ur packet is in good company.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(=
54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>As it hurtles through t=
he darkness at nearly the speed of light, our packet might pass by the occa=
sional curious fish or, if it's particularly unlucky, a shark. </span><a hr=
ef=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/968bc7d0-1fe6-464f-aebc-8c4990c09aad?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D""=
 style=3D"color: rgb(54,55,55);text-decoration: underline;">Sharks sometime=
s bite undersea cables</a><span>, though no one's quite sure why.</span></p=
><a class=3D"youtube-wrap" href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/73a60c40-d=
7ed-4e0e-803c-0de101dae7b9?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXep=
KbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" target=3D"_blank" data-component-name=3D"Youtube2ToDOMS=
